	(4,1,'2016-02-12 13:50:39','2016-02-12 13:50:39','Gold has lost its shine over the last few years, peaking in August 2011 at $1900 an ounce to lows of $1050 an ounce in mid-December 2015. Recent market volatility, low global interest rates and European banking credit woes has increased the value of gold to (close on Friday 12th February 2016) $1238 an ounce.\r\n\r\nGold is typically considered a secure investment in times of economic uncertainty and with global interest rates at all-time lows the opportunity cost of holding gold (gold has no yield) has become more attractive. In the short term gold could continue to be well-supported by a weaker US dollar, a slowing global economy and heightened fears of global indebtedness.\r\n\r\nIt was another tough weak for global and domestic markets with some relief on Friday, the Chinese stock market re-opens on Monday after celebrating the Lunar New Year.\r\n\r\nAs always we welcome any feedback on our Weekly Review.','Gold','','publish','open','open','','gold','','','2016-04-04 20:20:47','2016-04-04 19:20:47','',0,'http://strategiq.co.za/?p=4',0,'post','',0),
