	(53,1,'2016-04-01 20:04:56','2016-04-01 19:04:56','The 1<sup>st</sup> Quarter of 2016 was a volatile period for both local and international financial markets. The key focus areas included the slowdown in China (soft or hard landing?); the US recovery (how many rate hikes and how quickly) and European banking woes (amongst others). The response to each of these fears was allayed by central banks ranging from the Federal Reserve, to the European Central Bank (ECB) and policymakers in China leading many market participants to question whether central banks will be able to continue their simulative policies and at what future cost. An alternative view is that the US recovery is real (certainly supported by Fridays unemployment numbers); that China is adjusting from an export driven economy to a more consumer driven economy and that Europe is holding together through some challenging events. At StrategiQ we are more aligned with the latter, our base case scenario is that the US recovery continues to progress and ultimately helps global growth prospects. We expect market volatility to continue but at “almost” zero interest rates in developed markets we do not see an alternative to staying invested in high quality equities with sustainable growth prospects; superior cashflow generation and strong balance sheets.\r\n\r\nThe chart above illustrates the performance of the larger global indices: S&amp;P 500 (largest 500 companies in the US – green); MSCI World Index (basket of global indices – orange); EuroStoxx (largest European listed shares – purple) and the Nikkei 225 (largest 225 Japanese equities – blue). As highlighted above there was a significant pullback intra quarter with most indices recovering towards the end of the quarter.\r\n\r\nIn the attached weekly review, we cover local markets and how the larger sectors performed over the quarter.\r\n\r\nAs always we welcome any feedback on our Weekly Review.','1st Quarter 2016','','publish','open','open','','1st-quarter-2016','','','2016-04-04 20:05:33','2016-04-04 19:05:33','',0,'http://strategiq.co.za/?p=53',0,'post','',0),
