	(57,1,'2016-03-18 20:05:47','2016-03-18 20:05:47','Last week the ECB surprised with further loosening of monetary policy (reducing rates and increasing bond buying) and this week while the US Federal Reserve didn’t surprise in leaving rates unchanged, they did alter their outlook for 2 further rate hikes this year instead of 4, increasing the attractiveness of equities and riskier assets (emerging markets). In SA the Reserve Bank hiked rates by 25 basis points which helped strengthen the Rand to end the week at R15,25 (it was as high as R16,24 to USD intra week).\r\n\r\nGlobal markets continued to gain over the week with the major US indices turning positive for the year.\r\n\r\nAs always we welcome any feedback on our Weekly Review.','Rates hiked by 25 basis points','','publish','open','open','','rates-hiked-by-25-basis-points','','','2016-04-04 20:07:09','2016-04-04 19:07:09','',0,'http://strategiq.co.za/?p=57',0,'post','',0),
