	(61,1,'2016-03-04 20:07:55','2016-03-04 20:07:55','As per the chart above (and the longer dated chart of the week in our attached weekly review) it was a positive week for emerging markets, South Africa benefitted from the recent surge in commodity prices and improving global sentiment. Over the weekend Premier Li announced a 6.5% - 7% expansion goal for the Chinese economy. Whilst this and other central bank interventions of late has supported the recent gains in commodity prices we remain sceptical of this bounce. We would like to see more evidence of supply side “production cuts” and more consistent demand to buy into a revival in the commodity sector. However, the positive effect of these commodity gains for South Africa and other emerging markets is clearly visible in this week’s charts.\r\n\r\nGlobal markets continued to perform with most markets enjoying a strong week.\r\n\r\nAs always we welcome any feedback on our Weekly Review.','Emerging markets bounce back!','','publish','open','open','','emerging-markets-bounce-back','','','2016-04-04 20:09:03','2016-04-04 19:09:03','',0,'http://strategiq.co.za/?p=61',0,'post','',0),
