	(373,2,'2017-03-15 15:03:02','2017-03-15 13:03:02','Adcock announced a strong set of interim results, confirming our thesis that they are successfully on track to turning the business around.\r\n\r\nEvery segment showed positive growth with revenue overall increasing by 11% while HEPS increased 49%.\r\n\r\nListening to the CEO, he proved to be on top of the business from all angles, with a clear knowledge of each segment, exactly where future growth opportunities lie and how they plan to achieve this.\r\n\r\nThe sales and marketing team proved to be impressive by not only selling and marketing their portfolio but also successfully performing market research showing how consumer spending has changed. This has allowed them to focus and benefit on areas such as small sachet products.\r\n\r\nWhen questioned whether the recent currency strength would benefit profits in the second half (as the ZAR has strengthened significantly) the CFO clearly stated that owing to contracts already in place such a benefit will only show 3-6 months later (something to watch for going into the first half of 2018).\r\n\r\nAdcock is proving to meet Strategiq\'s investment criteria, where we seek to invest in strong, competitive, financially sound businesses with growing cash flow, run by good operating managers.','Adcock Turns Corner','','publish','open','open','','adcock-turns-corner','','','2017-03-15 15:03:02','2017-03-15 13:03:02','',0,'http://strategiq.co.za/?p=373',0,'post','',0),
