	(678,2,'2017-08-19 09:21:36','0000-00-00 00:00:00','The JSE All-Share index ended the week marginally higher, gaining +0.27%. Industrials (+0.81%), Financials (+0.23%) and SA Listed Property (+0.28%) all ended the week positively, whilst resources lost -0.81%. The All Share Index received a midweek boost after Tencent, 34% owned by JSE heavyweight Naspers, reported a robust 2Q17 set of results which were ahead of analyst expectations.\n\nIn economic news, SA retail sales rose 2.9% YoY, more than market expectations of 2.4%. In the previous month, retail sales had recorded a rise of 1.6%.\n\nGlobally, what was to be a relatively quiet week, was sadly disrupted with yet another terrorist attack. Seven people, including a police officer, were injured in the vehicle attack in Cambrils - hours after a rampaging van driver left 13 people dead and more than 100 wounded around 70 miles away in Barcelona.\n\nGeopolitical tensions between the US and North Korea faded over the week, resulting in markets shifting their attention to economic news out of Europe and the US Fed’s July meeting minutes.  Eurozone 2Q17 second estimate of GDP rose 2.2% on a YoY basis, more than market expectations of 2.1% (preliminary figures had recorded a rise of 2.1%), whilst Eurozone CPI was recorded at 1.3%, in line with expectations. The FOMC’s July meeting minutes showed a divided Fed, as one group of Fed policymakers felt inflation is still low and argued for caution in raising interest rates. Others expressed concerns that delaying further rate hikes could push inflation higher into dangerous territory.\n\nUS markets ended the week in negative territory with the Dow Jones (-0.84%), S&amp;P 500 (-0.65%) and NASDAQ (-0.64%) all losing value whilst their European counterparts including the FTSE 100 (+0.19%) and Stoxx 600 (+0.55%) achieved modest gains. The rand ended the week firmer against its major currency counterparts.\n\n<strong>Market Moves of the Week:</strong>\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-679\" src=\"http://strategiq.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/19-Aug-2017.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"499\" height=\"525\" />\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong> </strong></p>','Week in Review: Bitcoin surges above $4400','','draft','open','open','','','','','2017-08-19 09:21:36','2017-08-19 07:21:36','',0,'http://strategiq.co.za/?p=678',0,'post','',0),
