	(740,2,'2017-10-01 16:15:32','2017-10-01 14:15:32','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The JSE All-Share index (-0.47%) ended the week lower. Resources (+0.27%) were slightly positive, supported by the weaker rand (+2.32%). Industrials (-0.14%), Financials (-1.75%) and SA Listed Property (-2.53%) all contributed to the softer week.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In company news, South Africa’s largest company Naspers is increasing it’s investment in Delivery Hero, a German online food delivery service. Naspers will purchase a further 13% stake in the company from Rocket Internet for a consideration of R10.5bn. This will take the groups shareholding to 23.6%, making them the largest shareholder.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The South African central bank has told top lenders they cannot fire auditor KPMG -The disgraced auditing firm, still reeling from losing major clients due to their business relationship with Gupta-linked companies - as this might undermine the nations financial stability. KPMG sacked its South African leadership team two weeks ago and will ask a senior legal figure to conduct an external investigation into whether or not its South Africa-based workers were involved in any illegal activities.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The rand depreciated by 2.32% relative to the dollar, this coupled with increasing oil prices (Brent Crude up 1.20%) is a worrying sign for local consumers.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Globally, all major markets ended the week in the green. Gains in the Dow Jones (+0.25%), S&amp;P 500 (+0.68%), NASDAQ (+1.07%), STOXX 600 (+1.29%) and the FTSE 100 (+0.85%) all contributed to the stronger week.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The major global news of the week comes out of Germany, where chancellor Angela Merkel clinched her fourth term as chancellor of Germany. The win was no walk in the park as her Christian Democratic Union support plunged to a historic low of 33%, forcing her to form coalitions with smaller parties.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The majority of the headlines however were dominated by the far-right AfD party. The party captured 13% of the vote, meaning more than 90 members of the party will enter the Bundestag. The rise of the populism groups has no doubt been spurred on by the election of Donald Trump as the U.S. president.</p>\r\nElsewhere in Europe, Spanish government are fighting the Catalan government in a bid to secure Catalan independence. Spain\'s central government has issued stern warnings against the referendum, which the country\'s highest court has barred as unconstitutional. It has seized ballot papers and drafted thousands of extra police, or Guardia Civil, in a bid to prevent it.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In company news, Walmart’s e-commerce site Jet.com is preparing to launch its own private-label brand. The company plans to introduce more than 60 food and household  items in the coming months. U.S. supermarket competition is very high as of late, with technology giants Amazon recently acquiring Whole Foods. The supermarket and consumer goods industry is changing at a rapid pace and this move from Walmart\'s Jet.com perfectly displays how traditional stores are adapting to their new environment.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Market Moves of the Week:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_743\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"493\"]<img class=\"wp-image-743 size-full\" src=\"http://strategiq.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/ChartOct01.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"493\" height=\"521\" /> Source: Thomson Reuters[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Chart of the Week:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_746\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"955\"]<img class=\"wp-image-746 size-full\" src=\"http://strategiq.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/COTWOct.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"955\" height=\"718\" /> As a result of the German ele