	(766,2,'2017-10-14 11:10:22','2017-10-14 09:10:22','On Friday, the Supreme Court of Appeal (SCA) dismissed an appeal by the National Prosecuting Authority (NPA) and President Jacob Zuma against a High Court order which set aside the decision to withdraw charges against the president. The SCA ruled that the decision to drop the charges against Zuma was irrational meaning that technically the NPA must recharge him. The rand responded favourably to this news, strengthening by +1.5% to the US Dollar on the day.\r\n\r\nIn company news, Sasol announced that it would look for other options to settle outstanding debt related to its black economic empowerment scheme. The news positively impacted Sasol’s share price.\r\n\r\nThe JSE All-Share Index ended the week +1.13% higher amid gains in Industrials (+1.32%) and Financials (+3.33%). Resources came under pressure, losing -1.87% of their value.\r\n\r\nGlobal markets were also modestly positive with the Dow Jones (+0.43%), S&amp;P 500 (+0.15%), NASDAQ (+0.24%), Stoxx 600 (+0.50%) and the FTSE 100 (0.17%) all marginally up, whilst the Topix (+1.27%) had a relatively stronger week. Brent Crude Oil and the gold price also advanced +2.79% and +2.35% respectively.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Market Moves of the Week:</strong><img class=\" wp-image-769 aligncenter\" src=\"http://strategiq.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Market-moves-14-Oct-2017-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"503\" height=\"543\" /></p>\r\nIn the UK, Prime Minister Theresa May, warned the British public to prepare for crashing out of the European Union (EU) with no deal, setting out emergency plans to avoid border meltdown for businesses. She further added that the UK would publish two white papers on trade and customs after Brexit.\r\n\r\nIn economic news, the Eurozone investor confidence index recorded a rise to 29.70 in October, higher than market expectations of an advance to 28.50. ECB President, Mario Draghi indicated that interest rates are likely to stay low for an extended period of time, in order to promote solid economic growth within the Eurozone. The Eurozone region has shown a strong return to growth throughout 2017.\r\n\r\nIn the US, minutes of the Federal Reserve’s (Fed) September meeting indicated that policymakers are leaning towards another interest rate hike before this year-end. However, a few policymakers expressed caution on the need for a December interest rate hike.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Chart of the Week:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_770\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"855\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-770\" src=\"http://strategiq.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/chart-of-the-week-13-Oct-2017.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"855\" height=\"644\" /> Euro area industrial production rose more than expected in August and increased by 1.4% relative to the previous month. This was accompanied by a 0.2 percentage point upward revision to July’s figure and signals further support to the view that the euro will grow by 2 percent this year.[/caption]\r\n\r\nAs always we welcome any feedback on our Weekly Review.\r\n\r\nHave a great week!\r\n\r\n<em>The information included above as well as individual companies and/or securities mentioned should not be construed as investment advice, a recommendation to buy or sell or an indication of trading intent on behalf of any Strategiq product. Strategiq Capital is an authorised financial services provider (FSP 46624).</em>','Week in Review: SCA dismisses Zuma appeal on corruption charges','','publish','open','open','','week-review-sca-dismisses-zuma-appeal-corruption-charges','','','2017-10-14 11:40:49','2017-10-14 09:40:49','',0,'http://strategiq.co.za/?p=766',0,'post','',0),
